cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR, cs.CL

This paper deals with the study of the spread of misinformation and fact-checking on social media, specifically Twitter. It involves the analysis of a diffusion network obtained from retweets produced by several hundred thousand accounts. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves the study of the structural and dynamic characteristics of the network, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy). The use of k-core decomposition and fact-checking detection could also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
